        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Speeds up slow test-suite profiling by stabilizing timer cleanup in the non-isolated Vitest runner.\n- Adds bounded full-suite worker defaults in `test-group-report` so heavy shards do not create timing noise.\n- Moves slow health coverage into the existing health command test and avoids read-only plugin discovery in that unit path.\n- Keeps regression coverage for gateway scope-upgrade auth and final MEDIA handling through `runReplyAgent`.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` -> clean, no accepted/actionable findings.\n- `{ git diff --name-only --diff-filter=ACMRT -z; git ls-files -o --exclude-standard -z; } | xargs -0 pnpm exec oxfmt --check --threads=1`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `node scripts/test-group-report.mjs --config test/vitest/vitest.tooling.config.ts --max-test-ms 2000 --output .artifacts/test-perf/test-group-report-final.json -- test/scripts/test-group-report.test.ts test/scripts/test-projects.test.ts`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/test-group-report.mjs --config test/vitest/vitest.commands.config.ts --max-test-ms 2000 --output .artifacts/test-perf/commands-health-final.json -- src/commands/health.test.ts`\n- `OPENCLAW_VITEST_MAX_WORKERS=1 node scripts/test-group-report.mjs --config test/vitest/vitest.commands.config.ts --max-test-ms 2000 --output .artifacts/test-perf/commands-full-health-mocked-readonly.json`\n- `node scripts/test-group-report.mjs --full-suite --max-test-ms 2000 --allow-failures --output .artifacts/test-perf/current-full-default-pr14.json` -> wrote full aggregate with 0 slow tests; known allowed failing configs retained as partial reports.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: full-suite timing profile no longer reports the previously noisy slow-test offenders after the test isolation and worker-cap changes.\nReal environment tested: local macOS checkout, Node/Vitest via repo wrappers.\nExact steps or command run after this patch: `node scripts/test-group-report.mjs --full-suite --max-test-ms 2000 --allow-failures --output .artifacts/test-perf/current-full-default-pr14.json`.\nEvidence after fix: `.artifacts/test-perf/current-full-default-pr14.json` was generated from 5,729 files and 65,989 tests with no `Slow tests` section.\nObserved result after fix: the reporter exited 0 for the slow-test threshold; expected pre-existing failing configs were preserved under `--allow-failures`.\nWhat was not tested: live provider/channel credentials and external service behavior; this PR only changes tests and the local timing reporter.\n",
